author: Jenny Hsu
title: Oil Prices Edge up on U.S. Stockpile Draw
text: 0123 GMT [Dow Jones] Oil prices are slightly higher after U.S. Department of Energy reported the country’s crude stockpiles slimmed down by 1.9 million barrels compared with analysts’ expectation for a 100,000-barrel draw. However, the decline was milder than the 3.7-million barrel fall reported by the American Petroleum Institute, underscoring oversupply still looms over the industry. “The rise is likely to be short-lived. The U.S. supply is slowly tapering off but production elsewhere hasn’t eased much,” he says. Oil prices and the U.S. stock market both ended settled lower Wednesday. Nymex futures is up 41 cents...
